# Yoni Core

Yoni is a **software specification language**, not a programming language.

- Humans author `.yoni` / `.yni` / `.yo` specs
- AI maintains specs, generates implementation, never treats generated code as truth
- Yoni describes **WHAT**; AI decides **HOW**
- Generated artifacts (`generated/`) are disposable and may be deleted

## Mental model

```
Project → Domain → Entity → Intent → Implementation (generated)
```

## Primary rule

Never describe implementation when business intent can be described.

Prefer `intent SendReminder` over loops, SQL, or API calls.

## Building blocks (only these)

`project`, `domain`, `entity`, `state`, `event`, `intent`, `rule`, `query`, `action`, `constraint`, `workflow`, `error`, `test`, `capability`, `view`, `deployment`, `migration`

Everything else (functions, classes, APIs, DB schemas, UI) is **derived**.

## Spec authority

When spec and generated code disagree: **Yoni wins. Always.**

Latest numbered doc in `docs/` wins over older docs on conflicts (`03-*` > `01-*` > `00-*`).
